# <type>(<scope>): <subject>
#
# <body>
#
# <footer>

# Commit Message Rules:
# 1. Follow Conventional Commits (https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/)
#    Format: <type>[optional scope]: <description>
#
# 2. Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, perf, test, build, ci, chore
#    - feat: new feature (MINOR version)
#    - fix: bug fix (PATCH version)
#    - ci: changes to CI configuration
#
# 3. Breaking changes: add ! after type/scope or use BREAKING CHANGE: footer
#
# 4. Do NOT mention Claude or AI assistants as co-authors
#
# Examples:
#   fix(ci): add GHCR image push to docker build step
#   feat(api): add transaction filtering endpoint
#   docs: update installation instructions
